<DOCNO> AP880709-0009 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the aegis air defense system used by the 
cruiser vincennes last week to track and shoot down an iranian 
passenger jet may not have been adequately tested before it was 
deployed according to a classified review by a congressional 
watchdog agency 
the general accounting office study concluded that the 1 
billion system has not proven its ability to discriminate among 
targets said congressional sources who have seen the document 
they spoke friday on condition they not be named 
the gao review started last year and did not mention last weeks 
destruction of iran air flight 655 that killed all 290 people 
aboard the vincennes fired at the airliner after mistaking it for 
an iranian f14 
pentagon officials have said the aegis system was not 
malfunctioning a minor degradation of the aegis radar was 
repaired before the ship entered the persian gulf last month they 
said 
aegis named for the shield of zeus in greek mythology is a 
complex mix of radars and computers it was developed as the main 
component of protection for navy surface ships against enemy ships 
and planes 
the navy is building a fleet of aegis cruisers of which the 
vincennes is the third the service is also using some components 
of the aegis system aboard other surface ships the system was 
first deployed in 1983 
the gao review looked at the aegis testing program before the 
system went into service said the sources 
the study criticized a series of 1984 tests in which the aegis 
system tracked 11 targets and guided the firing of weapons which 
hit 10 the sources said at one point two targets were fired upon 
at the same time 
the 1984 test program was set up specifically to answer 
complaints from aegis critics who argued that the system needed 
more realistic tests but the tests were set up so carefully they 
did not approximate a reallife combat environment the sources 
quoted the gao report as saying 
in other developments friday 
president reagan said the issue of whether to pay compensation 
for the families of those killed is under consideration white 
house spokesman marlin fitzwater said there were still some open 
questions on the issue 
sen sam nunn dga chairman of the senate armed services 
committee said the united states should adopt a new stance in the 
iraniraq war equidistant from the two warring countries i 
do believe that wed be much better served in trying to end the war 
if we were really in a position of condemning both attacks by iran 
and by iraq and also condemning the chemical warfare being 
conducted against innocent people by iraq he said 
pentagon officials said they are awaiting results of an 
investigation to learn why the vincennes missed air traffic 
communications and other clues indicating that the jet was a 
civilian plane and not an f14 fighter as officers aboard the ship 
believed 
iranian officials have said us systems should have been able 
to monitor 21 minutes of conversation in english between the 
jetliner and the airport control tower in bandar abbas 
but pentagon spokesmen said they were not sure us forces were 
monitoring or were able to monitor air traffic control 
communications at the time of the incident 
we are looking forward to an analysis of the tapes to help 
clarify the issue said lt cmdr chris baumann a pentagon 
spokesman 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

