<DOCNO> AP880709-0011 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
the legal services corp is defending its 
chairman against congressional allegations that he improperly used 
government funds for presidential politics personal business and 
to help destroy the agency 
the corporation in a prepared statement issued late friday 
said it has uncovered no evidence that would lend credence to 
insinuations of misappropriation by w clark durant iii 
rep bruce a morrison dconn outlined the allegations and 
called for the resignation of durant who has served as chairman of 
the agencys board since december 1984 and was an adviser to rep 
jack kemps failed presidential campaign 
hes been undermining the legal services corporation by 
personal and political activities at the expense of the 
taxpayers morrison charged 
rep robert w kastenmeier dwis chairman of the house 
judiciary subcommittee on courts civil liberties and the 
administration of justice agreed that the evidence appears to show 
significant improprieties in the financial management of the 
corporation 
its very unlikely that durant could explain these matters 
satisfactorily he said 
durant reached by telephone at his detroit law office denied 
the allegations and countered that the congressional attack was 
motivated by political and policy disagreements over the direction 
of the agency which funds legal assistance programs for the poor 
the corporation said that it discovered during its examination 
of the records that mr durant is entitled to approximately 
8800 in attendance fees which he has not claimed the agency 
said it was continuing to review records at the subcommittees 
request 
the agency said the congressional investigation is being used 
by some in an attempt to derail needed reforms in the delivery of 
governmentfunded legal services to the poor and to discredit the 
efforts of chairman durant 
morrison said a preliminary congressional investigation of 
corporation records covering an 18month period revealed that 
durant used legal services telephone credit cards to call kemp 
headquarters nine times and may have charged campaigntied trips to 
the agency morrison said there were 23 trips to washington charged 
to the agency that have no documentation tying them to legal 
services work 
durant also charged to the agency longdistance phone calls to 
highranking federal transportation officials an apparent link to 
his private sector post as a railroad trustee morrison alleged 
and the congressman said durant is the man behind the 
agencys controversial move to hire lobbyists who were instructed 
to urge lawmakers to cut the legal services budget the general 
accounting office said last month that federal law prohibits such 
lobbying 
morrison added that documents provided by durant at the 
subcommittees request showed dozens of calls to private 
conservative organizations that have advocated the abolition of 
legal services including the heritage foundation dismantling 
legal services was an early goal of president reagan who appointed 
durant and the chairman has been a leading critic of his own 
agency 
morrison who headed a legal services program in new haven 
conn before his election to congress in 1982 estimated the cost 
of questionable telephone calls at more than 5000 plus 
thousands more in air travel 
durant scoffed at the allegations this is purely rooted in 
policy and political differences he said 
i dont have anything to hide he said if there are 
any calls that are not strictly related to legal services i have 
no objection and think the corporation should be reimbursed 
but he said those would not come close to the dollar estimates 
provided by morrison 
durant said he knew of 235 in telephone calls that were 
mistakenly charged to the agency and he said he knew of no travel 
expenses 
the decision to hire the lobbyists was made by john h bayly 
jr then president of legal services durant said but the 
congressmen said durant was behind the move to hire the lobbyists 
and then orchestrated a move to force bayly out of his job 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

