<TEXT>
the episcopal churchs policy making bodies 
friday approved a resolution to let the presiding bishop name a man 
to perform some sacramental acts for members who object to having a 
female bishop 
approval of the measure was in doubt briefly friday after a 
minor amendment was tacked onto it by the house of delegates one 
of two bodies meeting at the churchs 69th general convention here 
through monday but the house of bishops the churchs other 
legislative body concurred later friday 
while some at the meeting saw the resolution as watering down a 
1976 decision approving the ordination of women it sets a sixyear 
time limit on the authority to name a visitor as the man would 
be called 
the resolution was approved 12294 in the house of delegates and 
14028 in the house of bishops 
there are no women yet serving as bishops in the episcopal 
church but about 900 female priests have been ordained 
im sorry that the statement was accepted im glad there is a 
time limit i can live with it said the rev terry meadows a 
female priest from southern ohio 
patricia house a lay member of the house of deputies from san 
diego said the time limit undermines the episcopate in the long 
run i feel that a woman bishop would hasten the day of 
understanding 
the rev robert carey of the east oregon diocese backed the 
proposal and its limit 
i think the death of a belief is as painful as the death of a 
relationship he said there is a belief system dying we need 
to be concerned during grieving process and reach out as often as 
we can 
also on friday 
the house of bishops approved a resolution in response to a 
call by anglican archbishop desmond tutu to boycott american 
companies doing business in south africa the resolution goes to 
the house of delegates 
the house of bishops unanimously approved an economic 
development package that passed the house of deputies on wednesday 
and calls for 250000 from the church over the next three years to 
create community land trust cooperative housing employeeowned 
businesses and community credit unions 
</TEXT>
