dudley moore says his sensitivity to alcohol 
abuse tempered his portrayal of the lovable lush arthur in the 
sequel arthur 2 on the rocks 
moore who won an oscar nomination for his performance as the 
drunken millionaire arthur bach said his approach to the character 
this time was different because of a heightened awareness of 
alcoholism 
there was no official pressure from the studio or from any 
organized groups moore said recently but i personally have an 
educated awareness of the problem 
the producers also avoided any scenes in arthur 2 on the 
rocks of arthur drinking and driving unlike the original in 
which arthur is seen cruising in his rolls royce swigging from a 
bottle 
theres a scene in which linda liza minnelli says she never 
lets him drink and drive moore said and you can tell that 
arthur knows exactly what he should or should not do he still gets 
very drunk but thats because he feels panicked and isolated 
sometimes and unable to cope with the world 
but moore is quick to point out that the film doesnt preach 
the sequel opened friday at theaters nationwide 
