cancer 
a native of fort worth texas phillips became a public defender 
of the agency following his retirement from clandestine service in 
1975 his actions came when the agency suffered criticism for a 
number of abuses including charges of domestic spying 
he undertook the oneman public relations campaign after a 
discussion with his 15yearold daughter in which he revealed his 
true occupation an undercover intelligence officer but thats 
dirty was her response 
a former actor who served as an army air force gunner in world 
war ii phillips escaped from a german prisonerofwar camp after 
being shot down over austria in 1944 after the war phillips 
purchased an english language newspaper in chile where he was 
recruited by the agency 
during his quarter of a century with the cia phillips served as 
station chief in venezuela brazil and the dominican republic he 
operated a radio station on an island off the coast of cuba in the 
early months of fidel castros rule and did undercover duty in 
guatemala mexico city and beirut 
