if the work is deemed suitable for women workers according to 
the official china daily 
it said the regulations stipulate the kind and intensity of work 
suitable to women and bar them from laborintensive jobs such as 
mining and leathermaking the criteria used in determining what 
jobs were suitable was not given 
the regulations were drafted by the ministries of labor and 
public health the allchina trade union and the allchina womens 
federation and have been approved in principle by the state 
council the top executive body the report said 
the rules guarantee women the right to refuse job assignments 
that could harm their health allow one year of maternity leave 
with 90 paid days up from the current 56 and guarantee rest 
periods for pregnant and menstruating women and those who have just 
had abortions 
the newspaper did not comment on the possibility that the 
