<TEXT>
a un official today called for a 
sept 1 ceasefire in afghanistan and establishment of an interim 
afghan government that would exclude guerrillas or officials under 
marxist president najib 
un envoy diego cordovez making his comments a a news 
conference after returning from the afghan capital of kabul said 
the proposed government would consist of recognized independent 
and impartial afghans 
cordovez said the new government would be effective sept 1 
when a ceasefire would go into effect and that it would convene a 
grand council of leaders no later than march 1 
the grand council is a traditional afghan decisionmaking body 
whose leaders were chosen according to the countrys tribal 
structure 
cordovez said he believes such a council would be able to 
establish a government with broadbased support while najibs 
national reconciliation plan and attempts by supporters of the 
guerrillas to generate mass support have failed 
the guerrillas did not immediately comment on cordovez peace 
plan but a spokesman for a moderate guerrilla group opposed any 
negotiations with the communist afghan government 
we will not have anything to do with communists any kind of 
communists said azim nasserzia of the national islamic front 
of afghanistan 
he also called for a coolingoff period in the fighting 
before sept 1 during which the interim government would be 
chosen afghan guerrilla leaders backed by china pakistan and the 
united states have insisted that they will continue to fight until 
soviet troops are out of afghanistan and the kabul government is 
toppled 
i doubt whether there could be a coolingoff period said 
ikram gran spokesman for the sevenparty afghan alliance which 
has its headquarters in pakistans northwestern city of peshawar 
gran said however that he and nasserzia both supported the 
selection of the independent and impartial representatives 
they suggested the new leaders could be chosen among former cabinet 
ministers and officials now living in exile 
cordovez returned to islamabad friday from kabul where he met 
with najib other afghan leaders and soviet gen valentin verenikov 
