friday us ships should protect american merchant vessels british 
warships protect their nations cargoes and so on 
what weve had is a great escalation and we only get 10 
percent of our oil from the gulf and a tilt toward iraq adams 
said 
with the us navy admittedly in a combat zone adams said the 
reagan administration should formally invoke the war powers act 
giving congress the power to decide whether the warships should 
remain there 
this concern was clearly heightened by the downing of the 
iranian jetliner but even last november the staff of the senate 
foreign relations committee warned the united states seriously 
risks being drawn into war in the persian gulf although the stated 
purpose of the large american fleet in the region is narrowly 
defined to escort usflagged vessels through the gulf this 
mission given the circumstances is dangerously nebulous 
on the diplomatic front a year ago secretary of state george p 
shultz led a successful drive in the united nations security 
council for adoption of a ceasefire resolution 
but he has failed to persuade the soviet union or china to 
promise not to use their veto powers to block a followup 
resolution to impose an arms embargo against iran for refusing to 
negotiate with iraq 
as a result the ceasefire resolution is an empty statement of 
principle 
